2026-03-25 | Equal Sum Partition by One Cut

	Question
Return true if such a cut exists, otherwise false.

	Approach
1.	Compute total sum of matrix.
2.	If total sum is odd → impossible → return false.

3.	Try horizontal cuts:
		- Compute prefix sum row by row  
		- If prefix == total/2 → return true  

4.	Try vertical cuts:
		- Compute prefix sum column by column  
		- If prefix == total/2 → return true  

5.	If no valid cut found → return false.

	Time Complexity
	O(m × n)

	Space Complexity
	O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    bool canPartitionGrid(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {

        int m = grid.size();
        int n = grid[0].size();

        long long total = 0;

        for(int i=0;i<m;i++)
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
                total += grid[i][j];

        if(total % 2 != 0) return false;

        long long target = total / 2;

        // horizontal cuts
        long long sum = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<m-1;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<n;j++)
                sum += grid[i][j];

            if(sum == target) return true;
        }

        // vertical cuts
        sum = 0;
        for(int j=0;j<n-1;j++){
            for(int i=0;i<m;i++)
                sum += grid[i][j];

            if(sum == target) return true;
        }

        return false;
    }
};

	Key Insight
A valid cut simply splits total sum into two equal halves.  
By scanning rows and columns cumulatively, we can check all possible cuts efficiently in O(m × n).
